<h2 class="bold font-l">Did You Not Recognize Me?</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
The &quot;The Legends of Heroes: Trails of Cold Steel&quot; games certainly have no shortage (get it?) of jokes when it comes to the stature of Towa Herschel, one of the game's smallest cast members despite being 21 years of age. Upon arrival at the town that is the base of his new workplace, Leeves, Rean Schwarzer is brought up short (see what I did there?) by the arrival of Towa. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownHereShot" class='trope-example-link'>"Down Here!" Shot</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="px9rgs" data-video-descrip="In the &amp;quot;The Legend of Heroes&amp;quot; games, the characters use the ARCUS like a phone, and like a phone, nobody seems to say goodbye. In the case of Professor Schmidt from Cold Steel III (Sen No Kiseki III), he can't even be bothered to say &amp;quot;hello,&amp;quot; but then again, he has always been rather demanding." data-video-title="Demanding, As Always" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/px9rgs_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/px9rgs.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/TVTelephoneEtiquette" data-video-tropename="TV Telephone Etiquette" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/TheLegendOfHeroesTrailsOfColdSteel" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/px9rgs.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Demanding, As A...</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="h8o7jp" data-video-descrip="&amp;quot;So This is Basically&amp;quot; parodies the tendency of &amp;quot;The Legend of Heroes: Trails of Cold Steel&amp;quot; games to load you up with party members, such that by the final game you have access to a roster of no less than 39 playable characters (guests included) or &amp;quot;5000&amp;quot; as they quip here." data-video-title="5000 Party Members" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/h8o7jp_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://mediaproxy.tvtropes.org/width/250/https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/5000_party_members.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/LoadsAndLoadsOfCharacters" data-video-tropename="Loads and Loads of Characters" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/TheLegendOfHeroesTrailsOfColdSteel,WebAnimation/SoThisIsBasically" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://mediaproxy.tvtropes.org/width/250/https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/5000_party_members.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">5000 Party Members</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="kig5j8" data-video-descrip="As Brendan Blaber briefly sums up in his recent video on the Trails of Cold Steel series, the games have a significant amount of side content that the player can permanently miss if they aren't too careful." data-video-title="You have missed 45 QUESTS!" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/kig5j8_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/kig5j8.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/PermanentlyMissableContent" data-video-tropename="Permanently Missable Content" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/TheLegendOfHeroesTrailsOfColdSteel,WebAnimation/SoThisIsBasically" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/kig5j8.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">You have missed...</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="46ipgo" data-video-descrip="In &amp;quot;The Legend of Heroes: Trails of Cold Steel II,&amp;quot; Rean's party is stopped at the gates of Bareahard by a pair of soldiers who have a wanted list of people who may be plotting against the Noble Alliance. Good thing they have Emma with them, to mind trick the soldiers that they're just common travelers and most certainly aren't on any list of theirs. &amp;quot;Why're you still standing there?&amp;quot; Go along inside.&amp;quot;" data-video-title="Just Common Travelers" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/46ipgo_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/46ipgo.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/JediMindTrick" data-video-tropename="Jedi Mind Trick" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="VideoGame/TheLegendOfHeroesTrailsOfColdSteel" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/46ipgo.jpg">
